headline: Anthropic's AI push raises analyst concerns over Indian IT services revenues
summary: Rapid advances in artificial intelligence, triggered in part by Anthropic's latest automation push, could structurally erode the IT sector's high-margin application services revenues, creating downside risks ​to earnings and valuations, analysts warn.  Shares in India's software exporters settled 0.6% lower on ‌Thursday, a day after plunging 6% in their worst session for nearly six years, as AI-driven automation from U.S.-based Anthropic and ‌Palantir fuelled fears of compressed project timelines and disruption to the industry's labour-intensive business model.  The weakness has echoed across global IT stocks this week, extending a broader selloff in companies seen as most exposed to potential AI disruption.
